comments: Anderson's (ATL) arm is collapsed to his body when he absorbs the oncoming body contact with Brown (MIL) during his driving shot attempt.
Brown (MIL) makes incidental contact to the arm of Young (ATL) after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Anderson (ATL) reaches in and cleanly dislodges the ball from Connaughton (MIL) after he gathers the rebound.
Collins (ATL) slightly extends his forearm into Connaughton's (MIL) body but the contact is marginal and does not affect his ability to get to the rebound.
[Observable in Enhanced Video] Collins (ATL) begins to gather the ball and pins it against his leg before resuming his dribble in transition.
[Observable in Enhanced Video] Collins (ATL) leaves the floor with possession of the ball and his right foot lands prior to him releasing the ball during his pass attempt.
Lopez (MIL) briefly engages with Anderson (ATL) while setting the pick.
Len (ATL) places a hand on Brown's (MIL) back but the contact is marginal. Len (ATL) makes incidental contact to the arm of Brown (MIL) after the release that does not affect his play at the basket.
Frazier (MIL) moves laterally into Young's (ATL) path during the drive and the contact affects his SQBR.
Anderson (ATL) cleanly dislodges the ball from Brown (MIL).
Lopez (MIL) makes contact to Bembry's (ATL) body which affects his driving shot attempt.
Collins (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position during Brown's (MIL) driving shot attempt.
Bembry (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position on Brown (MIL) and makes contact with the ball as he reaches in during his dribble.
Bembry (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position on Brown (MIL) at the end of the drive.
Brown (MIL) is firming up and delivers slight contact to Collins (ATL)  while setting the screen.
Wilson (MIL) makes contact to Bembry's (ATL) arm during his shooting motion that affects his play at the basket.
Wilson (MIL) puts two already extended arms to Young's (ATL) back on the pick but the contact is marginal and doesn't affect his ability to defend.
Anderson (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position during the play at the basket by Ilyasova (MIL).
Young (ATL) takes more than two steps after he receives the pass.
LAR shows Collins (ATL) extends his arm and affects Ilyasova (MIL) defensive position.
Ilyasova (MIL) maintains a legal guarding position during the play at the basket by Collins (ATL) when he places a resting hand to Collins' back but does not deliver any contact.
Len (ATL) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Frazier (MIL) after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Huerter (ATL) and Hill (MIL) engage and separate during the rebound.
Ilyasova (MIL) maintains a legal guarding position on Young (ATL) at the end of the drive as he absorbs the marginal contact.
Frazier (MIL) makes marginal contact to Len's (ATL) body during his shooting motion that does not affect his play at the basket.
Ilyasova (MIL) establishes himself in a screening position in Anderson's (ATL) path as he absorbs the contact.
Anderson (ATL) gives Brown (MIL) room to land on the jump shot attempt.
RLS shows Connaughton (MIL) makes incidental contact to Len's (ATL) arm as he goes for the ball during the rebound.
Len (ATL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Hill (MIL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Len (ATL) could be deemed to be imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Frazier (MIL) has a resting hand on Young (ATL) during his shooting motion that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Frazier (MIL) firms up in a screening position in the path of Bembry (ATL) and absorbs the contact.
MOB shows Bembry (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position on Brown (MIL) and cleanly dislodges the ball on his steal attempt.
Bembry (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position on Brown (MIL) during the drive and the contact does not affect his SQBR.
Anderson (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Brown (MIL).
RLS shows Collins (ATL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Frazier (MIL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Lopez (MIL) maintains a legal guarding position on Collins (ATL) and cleanly breaks up the pass.
Hill (MIL) maintains a legal guarding position during the play at the basket by Young (ATL).
